rComments: His lectures are just reading the notes. The brightspace is extremely disorganized and his notes are hard to decipher. The upside is that the practice examples are exactly like the tests.

Very ok prof. He reads off lecture notes, does not solve problems in class. He breaks things down easily but his exams are marked tough. Use his old exams and go to dgds to solve the problems bc they will come up on the midterms and final. Hes ok, tries to be funny but uses a lot of satanic references so beware if that makes u uncomfortable.

Provides good examples and practice tests that strongly reflect the actual midterms/tests (no surprises!). Definitely recommend going to DGDs as the TAs do a really good job of explaining examples and all the steps. Midterms and exams were very fair.

Dr. Rada is super caring and always explains things clearly if you have any questions. The exams are also very fair. There are a lot of practice problems and if you do them, you will definitely ace the exams. Attending DGD is also very helpful.

Thick accent but is able to get the material across well. He is light-hearted and funny which creates a nice environment in the classroom. Study hard as this is a lot of material to take in but his tests and exams are fair. overall a good guy
Took some time to get used to his accent, but once you do, you would love how amazing this guy is. Heavy lecture but he tried his best to do more examples in class.
